&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for enthusiastic and dynamic fulltime Health Visitors to work in the Banbury locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will work as part of a well-established, supportive, corporate skill mix team delivering a high-quality professional service to clients. Banbury Locality has a mixed, expanding and diverse population providing excellent Health Visiting experience where you will find every day is different. In Oxfordshire we offer the full Healthy Child Programme and work innovatively with our skill mix staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oxford Health Foundation trust provides excellent training, preceptorship and supervision for staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated, innovative Band 6 Health Visitors who can rise to a challenge, demonstrating excellent communication and leadership skills. Applicants should be willing and able to lead a skill mix team, and have a thorough understanding of their Health Visiting role particularly in relation to safe guarding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Informal visits are encouraged and welcome.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Full-time and par-time hours per week considered.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Alison Mawer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Locality Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: alison.mawer@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07917 791 821&lt;/p&gt;
